NDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\\n *  See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\\n *  limitations under the License.\\n *--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/\\n//--------------------------------------\\n// snappy-java Project\\n//\\n// OSInfo.java\\n// Since: May 20, 2008\\n//\\n// $URL$ \\n// $Author$\\n//--------------------------------------\\npackage org.xerial.snappy;\\n\\n/**\\n * Provides OS name and architecture name.\\n * \\n * @author leo\\n * \\n */\\npublic class OSInfo\\n{\\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\\n        if (args.length >= 1) {\\n            if (\\\"--os\\\".equals(args[0])) {\\n                System.out.print(getOSName());\\n                return;\\n            }\\n            else if (\\\"--arch\\\".equals(args[0])) {\\n                System.out.print(getArchName());\\n                return;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        System.out.print(getNativeLibFolderPathForCurrentOS());\\n    }\\n\\n    public static String getNativeLibFolderPathForCurrentOS() {\\n        return getOSName() + \\\"/\\\" + getArchName();\\n    }\\n\\n    public static String getOSName() {\\n        return translateOSNameToFolderName(System.getProperty(\\\"os.name\\\"));\\n    }\\n\\n    public static String getArchName() {\\n        return translateArchNameToFolderName(System.getProperty(\\\"os.arch\\\"));\\n    }\\n\\n    public static String translateOSNameToFolderName(String osName) {\\n        if (osName.contains(\\\"Windows\\\")) {\\n            return \\\"Windows\\\";\\n        }\\n        else if (osName.contains(\\\"Mac\\\")) {\\n            return \\\"Mac\\\";\\n        }\\n        else if (osName.contains(\\\"Linux\\\")) {\\n            return \\\"Linux\\\";\\n        }\\n        else {\\n            return osName.replaceAll(\\\"\\\\\\\\W\\\", \\\"\\\");\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static String translateArchNameToFolderName(String archName) {\\n        return archName.replaceAll(\\\"\\\\\\\\W\\\", \\\"\\\");\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1782409781599}]}\n1779:[tool-call] delta {\"path\":\"/home/mihailo/git/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.xerial.snappy/snappy-java/1.0.4.1/main/extracted/org/xerial/snappy/SnappyInputStream.java\",\"limit\":120}\n1780:[tool-call] end id=call_qiHbOiTMn5xS0bciWUqqkntf|fc_0b01435cdb5be1c0016a3d6a659db88193be035589333ca1a6 name=read args={\"path\": \"/home/mihailo/git/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.xerial.snappy/snappy-java/1.0.4.1/main/extracted/org/xerial/snappy/SnappyInputStream.java\", \"limit\": 120}\n1781:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating Native Image support**\\n\\nI'm considering how Native Image can support predefined classes if the bytecode is examined during the build. It seems like runtime class definitions could come from a resource with predefined settings. However, there's a rule advising against creating tests for behavior that relies on runtime bytecode generation, class definition, or loading. It's an interesting limitation, and I wonder how it affects testing practices in those environments.\\n\\n**Inspecting SnappyInputStream**\\n\\nI’m looking into the SnappyInputStream tests and I see there’s no active loader. It seems like I need to focus on behavioral richness, but maybe I'm overcomplicating that. Reducing complexity could help. I should also check out the stream constructors to pinpoint any issues, like whether there's a timeout involved. It’s a lot to juggle! I'll keep examining the details for clarity.\\n\\n**Evaluating testing strategies**\\n\\nI’m considering the use of JUnit nested tests with one top-level file. I can't fork per method unless Gradle maxParallel is adjusted, which feels tricky. But I wonder if dynamic-access coverage could aggregate in a child process if the agent is inherited via JAVA_TOOL_OPTIONS. Typically, agent options are passed to the test JVM, not the child. So, I can’t rely on that. Maybe using `SnappyLoader` through a public API is a potential option?\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0b01435cdb5be1c0016a3d6a37079881939cb12e3a481162b5\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"content\\\":[],\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqPWplIBP3IUt7m6dMhpbEqwJY73K3XYXMePzUoyhdM05BwKVx9GDWnF5ppE0LyDIUPeZ9D4tc_yujSoP9JjocOBU_550GTFZI8jVALxkuDenXE3IXdPZ2WVsUW1Y6zOBYNJ4VRuI9gCfpb6gkeqe1IqHgfGH8KMkYGsEmEgpiPwkZXVXmJ9Dor0i-baYVSfHc_KIrOHMhIGrM5pID9ng5u75_oo2HP6pe2kYQe1ZcSeJ28jDlsQyPv--DzE4tiDHyWNh0hq4L8vjkE4cLgbsGWwNqq4tby1BLRcp5Ei3xALMVh7TmdlK434HzJM2ahofr42XG1oNyw3_kUiHdpgtWk-JelLijFTPpz3QylAOO9oJFImgvidqsGU9zJWWWpim04f5oGgoItdtXyPOq2hDwLvU0ba2d-H6Uxel_ooevrxOWllLSu8nGcM4XnfLtmFr_aPzWjh55vxUi_FYhgwu3p-zI544o74czQiXSEdCtOtGTBi17l2Chv6kaPbx0TQcKRDV8HNe6lPzkyRGNpoijoRaX-3er3TKIudtsDex59Aqcess7yyStaMLpiBhZOjkxJ4FTcB5a2wEujYC0qMNfEt-xEXXWZrRfkMCW8x5VcPPvff5DkKEWKxQCb_tThaJCJXWTNTttoPg9saqjvc6FnkJ5WGWacIgWlkK2uJcBRUnz5hxARm0YVO22slHxBt014aw10DrK0r7vETRy00geBT9aBegsmlHMZAWhn-chWygWxwad0mx6kdv7HSVgDAtJI7KJaE_LPcqfMILzZYAxBSkyzxs5xq1s_la6R7EzkkO6dNG1QQuFb0yIvPiK8odPoSI0g5t7EpJYEGrcfiAryLlNWNVsaR4k0_0Fzsto8VI-B-oC367hSmMfeP020SO-WM2QrevFy31_ETnBA_mZLSh2IhP9QRA6lQZzDmEQS3brHJ13l7IGuAddFXDlZAEvu08Yew33hAWHj3sYl58sGUzqE67KbyvagKD5rlJYJQk4pMG7qloceMaO6YojFATPqMrulJMUMWAZ_uTgPeQKXXCWKauH2vumF036P7KentUcXhqAhzjq6EDPNyFchMf91Wau6cmHKtZWo4qvMWtWTZhwKB2Akmj24GKvsaOgrxxyL_d_vsrq3HSkphgYUtYC4WH-ZYXqp7m07ecE0johdg7gIcN_26gV_6JTBR2jpT1BynEIVes4fZPC_kxiZxQ5e8uEiJbTPpTDjJVIHw8A2n8KpVeWmNcS2kWzkWhM8RGQYnqFoEEK2GvnXqMatfI0GM2TCm2D4L_zWBn7fwUM-h-2An80iDnCCg1t-8SGvEjVTsg1rDYpLOfTTR6PabiIorCtjOzk2awMUheZWQ4gh79Sbo-o2eTw7qQUwz4lU1Q-uh2NP_CzvWPeodevIgOxhgPffdrVUqeBc6okXcfjrbyEw4jWWpKgsbS_W-f-8t8w3DgElmwlXUM_jRIaVusOGAF5BkiH26BAQ6fVKdefekHyfM6vvuPnKsRMNy2iqCnuL8KuIv3CAR80-IcylWwJhfRLbv0F1PgSamqmExCvmy3