 SnappyLoader Implementation**\\n\\nI’m wondering if setting \\\"useSystemLib=false\\\" after the system library branch could help, allowing SnappyLoader.load to recognize the API already in place, which would skip line 383. It feels complicated since bundling first and then switching to system libraries seems impossible due to API constraints. I could explore using reflection to \\\"unload\\\" components, but that might be restricted unless it's a public API. Keeping everything efficient could involve using a separate JVM within the Gradle test while ensuring the dynamic agent connects properly.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0b01435cdb5be1c0016a3d6c747ef88193867f17773d5de36d\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"content\\\":[],\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqPWyXHrTJ4GDH7QzYtTzYWuuH-RhWNDxXKk6W0NmRTq5IrVf2D3Aj0lTPJ8z8s6wccpPMX3WdmrtoswnBhB8UStK-kp9EGCkR00mr17t-4xLIs3StWQZLoDQBOr9ySRlLeJlYxQnfnCKgD5mFTqMiZLOlHX6E6ZVbXykz2xN_7_qxpEliZ2GA5rvmLpbeU4Nc8oN6_TCbuwATopW2Prbd5vFvBVTwyc1H8zfQKqvzxt-CInM_4mBTCQRDQ21grZ27h4eWnjcLmhbEmaR31_G1AAIFAf7UawXHaKS5waUM-mlMN2sTTkUh0eMU5us3bvoT1CQaKcHNEWI0zMSxiPg9NMfD6qnArBGnN2g4WPsCTmX01I5MHvJ_JWZgH_qz_QD1H5TXI7A8BeIpd_o8OgdTLsZ8ocUy-6DCLMpS9rG-UhqUqJjBQjfc3UTaLar2YU6Nm0mGxnGLwkIZdmVVY1YIBM6lUnykUFXynv34dNIgWAKIqv84v-vw3EDdclTwzidv-ZASsMZjCsR8dB8G8gfozTNsDbR2DqZsvAsNtojTUr2-U0JZ5nWDp7vwujV4cStl-hd1e3dPqbMgX0lXGbt7mOWe0jT7_Lp6IsjSPCF8HrZeZ4HykeR_nVuK9rKWtETGkeW4AS9VAx8fOIdHZpxDYVySmce91aqisCeW0NceAzqeCo46Z_CDQ7WFQ-_JzStOBwM8REFypmzbpVW0Ru-hyLucVo9SH2eotnO1GHSeYz8kEQXxqUiQXTruV6ytafC1ORX3zJjP4OuQ8cx9KhlIRWGZGZr6bNc-LshV7wfV9d8Hb6dX2PPO6DVUuKm2N1ae68stKrMTMfTO8luNebBK47liBe3ZyBhXq56rVGwfuOMA_N_kz1tpl4d5pRL9I-NaPfvlnmftVlRiR2iSdGJeutlxNME3PmcSIGCmH7djLTHEFiCi3lgYXdc2-eX_bKNprB2OIh-CGWPDSJ6d9EpMKykKue5Jj-LXXdrp5LBr349LSIhwWbEhWlsHLvz8xqo6lM-hQZXOXPZSKTPd0sm_zxcA8IJX8d9Iqpjww6yuguUkPlD2ZwMRy9nR8GUskH7hS5wzLidaTnQa29YE8rkpzIfJYY1yTN50PIkIvVLfKL03VIiBMoT0ot8M2kmP0ofBhBK_itFtPdypeXzSd_D2C1jaSqBD4B-APVPbHR_Sxg0w-cZKDLR7kP