ing test configurations**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about how the default `test` task and custom `systemLibTest` relate to each other. The dynamic coverage report seems to depend on `nativeTestCompile`, not just `test`. I'm also wondering if the javaTest relates only to the basic test. The Jacoco report includes the test task, so I might need to configure Jacoco for multiple test tasks, but that feels broad. Maybe a simpler approach is to use `tasks.withType(Test).configureEach { forkEvery = 1 }` and create a second test method.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Exploring Gradle Native Configurations**\\\\n\\\\nI need to compute the OS and architecture in Gradle. One idea is to copy the resource name from the jar. However, the `java.library.path` needs to be set before running tests. Am I also considering the native image runtime? For the `nativeTest`, using `System.loadLibrary` means I need the `java.library.path` to include the actual external library. I’m also thinking about what resources are necessary for `nativeTest` compilation.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_ABg0FmKsJ5mv35bqBEaaZ3iI|fc_0b01435cdb5be1c0016a3d6ccef1bc8193aec2693886b6eefb\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rg \\\"jacocoTestReport|executionData|tasks.named\\\\(\\\\\\\"test\\\\\\\"|javaTest\\\" tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle -n\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1125, \"output\": 2109, \"cacheRead\": 49664, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 52898, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1782410399976, \"responseId\": \"resp_0b01435cdb5be1c0016a3d6ca105448193a4dcbd0c604fd139\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_ABg0FmKsJ5mv35bqBEaaZ3iI|fc_0b01435cdb5be1c0016a3d6ccef1bc8193aec2693886b6eefb\", \"