 a bundled mode, while a new `systemLibraryTest` will run in system mode. I need to ensure the configuration handles dependencies properly too.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering task finalization**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about using `tasks.named('test') { finalizedBy systemLibraryTest }` to set up the finalization. However, I wonder if the jacocoTestReport depends on the `test` task — could that mean the finalizer runs before jacoco? Since finalized tasks run after the `test` but might impact the order of execution, I need to ensure the dependencies are correctly set up to avoid conflicts. It's a bit tricky, so I want to double-check my approach.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_SPTUeKaU36wY9xcyWhouQ5Z6|fc_0b01435cdb5be1c0016a3d6d0b5ffc8193be578e0f0d59967d\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rg \\\"javaTest\\\" -n build.gradle settings.gradle tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 469, \"output\": 2320, \"cacheRead\": 56320, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 59109, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1782410460854, \"responseId\": \"resp_0b01435cdb5be1c0016a3d6cddf4a8819396bd1c52d938ee80\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_SPTUeKaU36wY9xcyWhouQ5Z6|fc_0b01435cdb5be1c0016a3d6d0b5ffc8193be578e0f0d59967d\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle:167:// gradle javaTest -Pcoordinates=<maven-coordinates>  §TCK-test-harness.3\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle:168:tasks.register(\\\"javaTest\\\", JavaTestInvocationTask.class) { task ->\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1782410507897}]}\n5665:  // g